This module allows control of the profiles and global preferences firefox. Testing onFirefox 17 CentOS6.4.

-. Basically controls two files:
firefox.js file in /usr/lib64/firefox/defaults/preferences/ 
		or /usr/lib/firefox/defaults/pref/ 

firefox.cfg file in /usr/lib64/firefox/
		or  /usr/lib/firefox/
=======
This module allows control of the profiles and global preferences firefox. 
Testing on Firefox 17 CentOS6.4.

-. Basically controls two files:
####      firefox.js #####
CentOS/RedHat:   /usr/lib64/firefox/defaults/preferences/
Debian/Ubuntu:   /usr/lib/firefox/defaults/pref/ 


####     firefox.cfg #####
CentOS/RedHat:  /usr/lib64/firefox/
Debian/Ubuntu:  /usr/lib/firefox/
>>>>>>> 0628687adc6a48f7f5e9f112dc3240b3e86006a6

-. Depends:
CentOS/Redhat: EPEL repository or package firefox-17.0.8-1.el6.centos.x86_64.rpm
Ubuntu/Debian: sourcelist

<<<<<<< HEAD
-. One was developed for (CentOS/RedHat)6.4, however it can be exported to other platforms.
=======
-. One was developed for (CentOS/RedHat)6.4, however it can be exported to other
 platforms.

Content Files:
###########################################################
########  init.pp #########################################

 class firefox {
$Homepage='SERVERWITHHOMEPAGE'

include firefox::config
}
##########################################################
########  config.pp ######################################

 class firefox::config {
	case $operatingsystem {
      	/(CentOS|Redhat)/: { $pathfirefox = "/usr/lib64/firefox/defaults/preferences"}
      	/(Ubuntu|Debian)/: { $pathfirefox = "/usr/lib/firefox/defaults/pref" }
      	default: { fail("Unrecognized operating system for Firefox") }
}

	package {
	'firefox':
	ensure => installed,
}

	file {
	'firefox.cfg':
	path => "$pathfirefox/firefox.cfg",
	content => template('firefox/firefox.cfg.erb'),
	mode => 644,
	owner => 'root',
	group => 'root',
	require => Package['firefox'],
}

	file {
	'firefox.js':
	path => "$pathfirefox/firefox.js",
	source => 'puppet:///modules/firefox/firefox.js',
	mode => 644,
	owner => 'root',
	group => 'root',
	require => Package['firefox'],
}
	file {'/etc/firefox/':
	ensure => 'directory',
	group => 'root',
	recurse => true,
	force => true,
	mode => '775',
	owner => 'root',
	require => Package['firefox'],
}
	file {'/etc/firefox/profile/':
	ensure => 'directory',
	group => 'root',
	recurse => true,
	force => true,
	mode => '775',
	owner => 'root',
	require => [File['/etc/firefox/'],Package['firefox']],
}
	file {
	'bookmarks.html':
	path => '/etc/firefox/profile/bookmarks.html',
	source => 'puppet:///modules/firefox/bookmarks.html',
	mode => 775,
	owner => 'root',
	group => 'root',
	require => [File['/etc/firefox/profile/'],Package['firefox']],
}
}
>>>>>>> 0628687adc6a48f7f5e9f112dc3240b3e86006a6
##############################################################################

firefox.cfg.erb (firefox/templates/)

firefox.js  (firefox/files/)

bookmarks.html file can be generated from any firefox browser and copy files 
within the directory
